This paper deals with the topic of privacy in statistical databases, which is a common theme in computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides guidance for setting parameters, which is relevant to database management (cs.DB).
